cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CL. 

This paper proposes a model for computer vision tasks that utilizes recurrent attention and spatial transformer network. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also mentions the use of clues or constraints to improve the model's performance, which suggests that it may also belong to the categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the use of recurrent attention model implies that it may also belong to the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with image classification and inpainting tasks, which suggests that it may also belong to the category of cs.CL (Computation and Language).
